The sampling rate for each voice signal must be at least 6 kHz (twice the 3 kHz bandwidth). With 16 quantization levels, each sample requires 4 bits (since \(2^4 = 16\)).  

Thus each voice signal needs a bit rate of \(6 \times 4 = 24\) kbps, and with a minimum bit interval of 1 µs, the channel supports 1 Mbps. Dividing 1 Mbps by 24 kbps gives approximately 41.67, so the closest option is 45 signals.  

